The price of sachet water(better known as pure water ) may be increased anytime from now as the Association of Table water Producers in Ekiti has disclosed its plan to hike the price. The zonal  chairman, Oye/ Ikole, Hon Tale Oguntoyinbo, in a  statement made available to Independent on Sunday hinted that  the price of a bag of water has been increased  from N150, to N200 per bag with immediate effect. He explained that the current economic realities cannot allow the Association to stick to the old price OPWS Neutralises Militia Gang Leader, Two Bandits Wanted In… Supreme Court Voids Kwara State Government’s Land Seizure According to the release issued after the their meeting in Oye Ekiti, Oguntoyinbo said  for producers to be able to bring quality water to the door steps of our consumers with the current cost of materials for water production the price cannot be less than N200 per bag. The chairman who said water is important to everybody, and water is life, the cost of maintenance, and purchase of water materials are going up every day. Oguntoyinbo who argued that government had done nothing to ease the problems, neither to assist water producers in alleviating the problem. “A loaf of bread. Is now N400, a litter of petrol if available #200 to #300, nobody is complaining.  In order to satisfy our numerous customer we have no choice than to increase the price from N150 to N200. Hon Oguntoyinbo explained further that places where nylon and other materials for water are being produced with regular electricity, Lagos, Ibadan, Abuja and others, a bag of water is between N200 & N250. “Therefore, producers of water here cannot continue to suffer in silence. He said many Water producers cannot improve the condition of their factories, talkless of buying a new vehicle. ” the statement reads. POLL The chairman therefore appealed to members of the public to bear and reason with the association in view of the present economic crisis in the country.